tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE photos (
  photo_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  photographer_id UUID REFERENCES photographers(photographer_id),
  photo_url STRING,
  description STRING,
  date_uploaded TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE photos (
    photo_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photographer_id INT,
    photo_title VARCHAR,
    photo_description TEXT,
    date_taken DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (photographer_id) REFERENCES photographers(id)
);

CREATE TABLE awards (
    award_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photographer_id INT,
    award_name VARCHAR,
    award_category VARCHAR,
    award_year INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (photographer_id) REFERENCES photographers(id)
);

CREATE TABLE photos (
    photo_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photographer_id INT NOT NULL,
    photo_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    photo_description TEXT,
    upload_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (photographer_id) REFERENCES photographers(photographer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE camera_gear (
    gear_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photographer_id INT NOT NULL,
    gear_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    gear_description TEXT,
    purchase_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (photographer_id) REFERENCES photographers(photographer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE photo_comments (
    comment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    photo_id INT NOT NULL,
    commenter_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    comment TEXT,
    comment_date DATETIME NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (photo_id) REFERENCES photos(photo_id)
);

CREATE TABLE photographers (
  photographer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  phone_number VARCHAR(20),
  portfolio_url VARCHAR(200)
);

CREATE TABLE photos (
  photo_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  photographer_id INT REFERENCES photographers(photographer_id),
  photo_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  photo_description TEXT,
  upload_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE camera_gear (
  gear_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  photographer_id INT REFERENCES photographers(photographer_id),
  camera_brand VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  camera_model VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  lens_brand VARCHAR(50),
  lens_model VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE photo_locations (
  location_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  photo_id INT REFERENCES photos(photo_id),
  location_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  city VARCHAR(50),
  country VARCHAR(50)
);
